Heat oven to 425 degrees F. Cook ground beef with onion in large skillet over medium high heat, stirring occasionally, for 8 minutes or until no longer pink. Drain. Spread crust with sauce from packet. Crumble ground beef over sauce. Arrange pickle chips over pizza and top with cheese. Sprinkle bacon over cheese. Carefully place pizza directly on oven rack. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted and crust is crisp.